\mt1 Leviticus
\is1 Introduction
\ip The Latin word \bk Leviticus\bk* means ‘concerning the Levites’, who were the tribe of workers and priests who God chose serve him at the altar and in other religious ceremonies. Hebrew readers call this document ‘Vayikrā’ which is the first word in the Hebrew and means ‘And he called’ (Yahweh called Mosheh). Some European and other translations call it ‘The third book of Mosheh/Moses’.
\ip It's believed that of people Moses just the writer of this book there to Mountain Sinai at time of camped them there, because can be read this there to: 1:1, 4:1, 6:1,24, and of 8:1.
\ip The Libitiku document concerning this of correct behaviour of descendants of Yisrael/Israel so that eg-isipen them clean of God. The one means eg-isipen them clean of God is the sacrificing of desire of God.
\ip And/Now so that egkaay-ayaran indeed the sacrificing, mig-alam the god of person Aharon/Aaron and his descendants.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The laws concerning the offerings and of sacrifices \ior 1:1–7:38\ior*
\io1 The dedication of Aharon and of his children males so that to become priests \ior 8:1–10:20\ior*
\io1 The laws concerning the cleaning and of not clean \ior 11:1–15:33\ior*
\io1 The day of forgiveness of sin \ior 16:1-34\ior*
\io1 The laws concerning the pegpabecome_holy of birth and of worshipping \ior 17:1–27:34\ior*
